I was working on the NEMA-17 gearbox base today, and it took a lot more effort than I expected. I opened Autodesk Fusion planning to start, since I thought I had all the measurements, but then I realized I wasn’t sure about the bolt spacing. I double checked the measurements and dimensions on amazon and other websites, even though I thought I already knew the numbers. Then the sketch started acting up. One constraint kept moving, and I couldn’t figure out why, so I deleted half the sketch because I was kinda annoyed. I also got distracted by a random video I saw while researching about motor mounts, and it helped a little, since it gave me the idea to clean up the edges. The fillets were another whole debate in my head — I kept adding them, and removing them. At one point, a feature broke, and I had to undo a bunch of things, which made me feel like I had no idea what I was doing. But when everything finally lined up, and I was finally done with the base.
